WEBVTT

00:01.001 --> 00:03.337
PREVIOUSLY ON WHITE COLLAR...

00:03.371 --> 00:06.074
THESE MARSHALS ARE HERE TO TAKE
NEAL CAFFREY INTO CUSTODY.

00:06.107 --> 00:07.075
Peter: I GAVE NEAL
THE SIGNAL TO RUN.

00:07.108 --> 00:08.376
YOU SET HIM FREE?

00:08.409 --> 00:10.344
IF ANYTHING
WERE TO HAPPEN TO HIM,

00:10.378 --> 00:11.845
I DON'T THINK
I COULD LIVE WITH IT.

00:11.879 --> 00:15.416
AGENT BURKE,
I'M GOI TO FIND NEAL CAFFREY.

00:15.449 --> 00:17.218
AND YOU'RE GONNA
HELP ME DO IT.

00:17.251 --> 00:20.088
THE AGENT WHO IS AFTER YOU,
HIS NAME IS COLLINS.

00:20.121 --> 00:21.889
AND HE WON'T STOP
UNTIL HE FINDS YOU.

00:21.922 --> 00:23.157
HE'S DANGEROUS.

00:23.191 --> 00:25.159
Dobbs:
PARADISE COMES AT A PRICE.

00:25.193 --> 00:26.694
AND IF I HAVE A CONCERN,
I COME TO YOU.

00:26.727 --> 00:28.096
ANYTIME, DAY OR NIGHT.

00:28.129 --> 00:30.198
THEN I THINK
WE WILL BE VERY HAPPY HERE.

00:30.964 --> 00:32.900
CAFFREY'S FATE IS OUT
OF YOUR HANDS.

00:32.933 --> 00:34.535
DO YO UNDERSTAND?

00:34.568 --> 00:35.736
COMPLETELY.

00:35.769 --> 00:38.106
I'M LOOKING FOR A FRIEND.

00:38.139 --> 00:39.873
MAYBE YOU'VE SEEN HIM.

00:39.907 --> 00:41.509
HAS HE DONE SOMETHING?

00:41.542 --> 00:42.910
YOU CAN HAVE
ANY WOMAN YOU WANT,

00:42.943 --> 00:44.245
AND THE ONE WOMAN
YOU CHOOSE

00:44.278 --> 00:45.846
IS THE ONLY WOMAN
WHO DOESN'T WANT YOU.

00:45.879 --> 00:47.181
AGENT BURKE.

00:47.215 --> 00:49.016
NEVER MIND.
I'M SURE YOU HAVEN'T SEEN HIM.

00:49.049 --> 00:51.385
NOW, I'M OFFERING
$500,000 U.S.

00:51.419 --> 00:54.088
FOR THE CAPTURE OF THIS MAN.

00:54.122 --> 00:55.856
I REALLY THOUGHT I WAS DONE
RUNNING THIS TIME.

00:55.889 --> 00:57.191
YOU RUN, I RUN.

00:57.225 --> 00:59.393
THEN LET'S RUN.

01:03.264 --> 01:05.766
[ ENGINE REVS ]

01:17.745 --> 01:20.381
WE WERE SUPPOSED TO MEET NEAL
BACK AT THE WHARF.

01:20.414 --> 01:22.550
BY DAWN.
WE WAITED FOR HIM ALL NIGHT.

01:22.583 --> 01:23.584
HE DIDN'T SHOW UP.

01:23.617 --> 01:26.220
NEAL IS WELL AWARE HE'S
THE ISLAND'S MOST WANTED.

01:26.254 --> 01:28.055
NOW, IF YOU HAD READ
"TEAM THIEVING 101"...

01:28.088 --> 01:29.157
THAT DOESN'T EXIST.

01:29.190 --> 01:30.724
...WHICH CLEARLY
YOU HAVE NOT,

01:30.758 --> 01:33.394
YOU WOULD KNOW YOU DO NOT LEAVE
THE SET RENDEZVOUS POINT.

01:33.427 --> 01:35.496
AND IF YOU READ
"CATCHING NEAL CAFFREY 101,"

01:35.529 --> 01:38.098
YOU SHOULD KNOW THAT, FIRST,
YOU START WITH THE GIRL.

01:43.504 --> 01:45.439
SEÑORITA.

01:45.473 --> 01:48.342
BARRY, WHAT ARE YOU
STILL DOING HERE?

01:48.376 --> 01:49.243
BARRY?

01:49.277 --> 01:50.578
MY NOM DE PLUME.

01:50.611 --> 01:53.147
I THOUGHT YOU LEFT WITH NEAL
LAST NIGHT.

01:53.181 --> 01:54.615
THAT WAS THE PLAN.
I TAKE IT YOU SAW HIM?

01:56.450 --> 01:59.587
PETER.
WE MET YESTERDAY.

01:59.620 --> 02:01.755
I'M ON NEAL'S SIDE.

02:01.789 --> 02:02.990
HE IS.
BACK TO NEAL.

02:03.023 --> 02:04.492
HE WANTED TO MEET YOU BOTH,

02:04.525 --> 02:07.195
BUT THERE WERE TOO MANY PEOPLE
OUT LOOKING FOR HIM,

02:07.228 --> 02:08.662
SO HE WENT BACK TO DOBBS'.

02:08.696 --> 02:10.097
DOBBS?

02:10.130 --> 02:11.465
SHELTER
FROM THE STORM.

02:11.499 --> 02:13.434
OUR RESIDENT PROTECTOR
ON RETAINER.

02:13.467 --> 02:14.935
HE WENT THERE FOR COVER?

02:14.968 --> 02:16.937
HE DIDN'T INTEND
TO SPEND THE NIGHT.

02:16.970 --> 02:18.672
HE'S PROBABLY
STILL THERE.

02:18.706 --> 02:19.773
THANK YOU.

02:19.807 --> 02:22.710
WILL YOU LET ME KNOW
WHEN YOU FIND HIM?

02:22.743 --> 02:23.644
YEAH, OF COURSE.

02:24.978 --> 02:29.317
ONE THING I KNOW ABOUT NEAL --
HE KNOWS HOW TO RUN.

02:39.660 --> 02:41.595
[ CLICKING ]

02:49.237 --> 02:51.239
[ STRAINING ]

03:09.189 --> 03:10.190
[ NUT SQUEAKING ]

03:10.224 --> 03:11.325
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

03:11.359 --> 03:13.361
[ SQUEAKING CONTINUES ]

03:23.871 --> 03:25.906
[ SQUEAKING ]

03:35.949 --> 03:36.784
COME ON.

03:40.654 --> 03:44.292
[ DOOR OPENS,
INDISTINCT CONVERSATION ]

03:50.331 --> 03:52.032
Dobbs: SEE?

03:52.065 --> 03:54.535
JUST AS WE LEFT HIM.

03:54.568 --> 03:56.470
TWO MORE HOURS, CAFFREY.

03:56.504 --> 03:58.372
THEN IT'S ONLY A SHORT FLIGHT
TO THE CANARY ISLANDS

03:58.406 --> 03:59.707
AND AN EASY RIDE HOME.

03:59.740 --> 04:00.974
HERE.

04:09.116 --> 04:10.918
I CAME TO YOU
FOR HELP, DOBBS.

04:10.951 --> 04:13.587
Dobbs: I DON'T KNOW WHY.
I WOULDN'T HARBOR A FUGITIVE.
I PAID YOU.

04:13.621 --> 04:15.989
TO HELP ESTABLISH YOURSELF
ON THE ISLAND.

04:16.023 --> 04:18.292
YOU NEVER SAID THE U.S.
GOVERNMENT WAS LOOKING FOR YOU.

04:23.364 --> 04:25.633
YOU SHOULD GET THAT FIXED.

04:25.666 --> 04:27.935
I TOLD YOU
I DIDN'T WANT HIM HERE.

04:27.968 --> 04:31.271
CAFFREY, YOU ONLY HAD TO BE GOOD
FOR A COUPLE OF HOURS,

04:31.305 --> 04:33.674
AND AS LONG AS YOU GOT
TWO GOOD LEGS,

04:33.707 --> 04:35.676
YOU'RE GONNA FIND
A WAY TO RUN.
YOU'RE A FEDERAL AGENT.

04:35.709 --> 04:38.712
YOU WERE IN THE ACT OF FLEEING.
YOU COULD BE ARMED.

04:39.347 --> 04:40.948
OHH! GOD!

04:40.981 --> 04:42.450
NO MORE RUNNING, CAFFREY.

04:44.785 --> 04:47.355
AAH!

04:48.822 --> 04:49.790
[ GRUNTS ]

05:12.746 --> 05:15.683
I'M ASSUMING BIG BROTHER
DIDN'T GIVE YOU FULL ACCESS

05:15.716 --> 05:17.885
TO THEIR KEYHOLE
SATELLITE FOOTAGE.

05:17.918 --> 05:20.287
THIS TRIP DOESN'T HAVE
BIG BROTHER'S BLESSING.

05:20.320 --> 05:21.489
OH.

05:21.522 --> 05:24.392
LOOKS LIKE
THEY'RE SETTING UP A PARTY.

05:24.425 --> 05:26.794
DOBBS' MONTHLY
ISLAND-WIDE FETE.

05:26.827 --> 05:29.329
IT'S WHERE DOBBS
DISTRIBUTES HIS PAYOLA

05:29.363 --> 05:30.864
TO THE ISLAND OFFICIALS.

05:30.898 --> 05:33.701
QUITE THE ISLAND YOU'VE CHOSEN
FOR YOURSELF.

05:33.734 --> 05:36.970
LOOK, SUIT,
I-I NEED TO ASK YOU SOMETHING.

05:37.004 --> 05:40.641
ONCE WE GET OFF THIS ISLAND,
HYPOTHETICALLY,

05:40.674 --> 05:44.077
WHAT ARE YOUR EXACT INTENTIONS
WITH NEAL?

05:44.111 --> 05:45.479
LET'S FIND NEAL.

05:45.513 --> 05:48.516
THEN WE'LL DEAL
WITH THE REST OF THIS.

05:50.951 --> 05:52.853
MOZ, 11 O'CLOCK.

05:54.354 --> 05:56.356
COLLINS.

05:56.390 --> 05:58.225
BEST CASE --
COLLINS GOT A TIP,

05:58.258 --> 06:00.994
AND DOBBS
IS HIDING NEAL INSIDE.

06:01.028 --> 06:04.565
YEAH, WORST CASE,
DOBBS TURNED HIM OVER.

06:04.598 --> 06:06.199
HOW MUCH PROTECTION MONEY
DO YOU PAY DOBBS?

06:06.233 --> 06:08.335
OH.
[ CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKING ]

06:08.368 --> 06:09.937
APPARENTLY, NOT ENOUGH.

06:09.970 --> 06:12.506
ALL RIGHT, EVENTUALLY, THEY'RE
GONNA HAVE TO BRING NEAL OUT

06:12.540 --> 06:14.542
IF THEY WANT TO CATCH
THE NEXT FLIGHT OUT OF HERE.

06:14.575 --> 06:16.610
THAT'S WHEN
WE MAKE OUR MOVE.

06:18.211 --> 06:19.212
OHH, GOD.

06:19.246 --> 06:20.213
ALMOST GOT IT.

06:20.247 --> 06:22.783
[ SIGHS ]
THERE.

06:22.816 --> 06:25.619
HOW BAD IS IT?

06:25.653 --> 06:27.455
THE BULLET LODGED
IN THE VASTUS LATERALIS,

06:27.488 --> 06:28.889
THE THIGH MUSCLE
NEXT TO THE BONE.

06:28.922 --> 06:29.890
NO ARTERIES WERE HIT.

06:29.923 --> 06:31.291
THAT SOUNDS PROMISING.

06:31.324 --> 06:32.693
YOU GONNA STERILI--

06:32.726 --> 06:33.694
OKAY.

06:33.727 --> 06:34.762
AAH.

06:34.795 --> 06:36.363
IT'S GONNA HURT
FOR A FEW WEEKS,

06:36.396 --> 06:37.431
BUT YOU'LL HEAL UP FINE.

06:37.465 --> 06:40.868
LOOK AWAY.
FOCUS ON THE BOATS.

06:40.901 --> 06:43.136
ESMERELDA...

06:43.170 --> 06:45.038
ISABELLA...

06:45.072 --> 06:48.576
CLAUDIA, ANNETTE...

06:48.609 --> 06:50.043
WHAT ARE YOU SAYING?

06:50.077 --> 06:52.880
I'M ADMIRING YOUR BOATS.

06:52.913 --> 06:53.781
STAND UP.

06:53.814 --> 06:55.749
COLLINS IS WAITING
FOR YOU OUTSIDE.

07:01.589 --> 07:02.923
THANK YOU, DOCTOR.

07:05.258 --> 07:07.294
OH, GOD.

07:07.327 --> 07:09.062
WHOA.
STAY OFF YOUR FEET.

07:09.096 --> 07:10.230
I MEAN IT.

07:10.263 --> 07:12.299
DO NOT PUT
ANY PRESSURE ON IT,

07:12.332 --> 07:14.668
OR THAT WOUND
WILL OPEN UP AGAIN.

07:14.702 --> 07:15.936
WELL, THAT'S GONNA BE
A LITTLE TRICKY.

07:15.969 --> 07:17.137
YOU WANT ME
TO WALK TO THE CAR?

07:20.173 --> 07:22.910
BELIEVE ME, IT'S THE LAST TIME
I'LL ASK FOR YOUR HELP.

07:22.943 --> 07:23.977
Dobbs: GOOD.

07:24.011 --> 07:26.079
[ GRUNTS ]
YOU DIDN'T HAVE TO TURN ME IN.

07:26.113 --> 07:28.281
I JUST NEEDED TO CAMP OUT
FOR A COUPLE HOURS

07:28.315 --> 07:29.817
TILL I COULD MAKE IT
TO THE DOCKS.

07:29.850 --> 07:30.851
Dobbs:
THIS ISN'T A HALFWAY HOUSE.

07:30.884 --> 07:31.852
YOU JEOPARDIZED ME,
MY HOME.

07:31.885 --> 07:33.487
HOW MUCH
DID THEY OFFER YOU?

07:33.521 --> 07:34.655
I DON'T NEED MONEY.

07:34.688 --> 07:36.590
NO.

07:36.624 --> 07:39.026
NO, YOU NEED THE U.S. LAW
ENFORCEMENT OUT OF YOUR HAIR.

07:39.059 --> 07:40.528
WHY?

07:40.561 --> 07:42.696
THEY'RE LOOKING FOR YOU,
NOT ME.

07:42.730 --> 07:44.865
LET'S GIVE THEM
WHAT THEY WANT.

07:46.299 --> 07:47.200
OH, GOD.

07:51.805 --> 07:55.543
Peter: THERE'S NEAL,
AND HE'S ZIP-TIED TO THE DASH.

07:55.576 --> 07:57.778
OH.
AND THERE'S COLLINS.

07:57.811 --> 07:58.979
THEY'RE HITTING THE ROAD.

07:59.012 --> 08:01.114
YOU SURE THIS PLAN OF YOURS
WILL STOP HIM?

08:01.148 --> 08:02.550
DOES A WINE HAVE TANNINS?

08:15.195 --> 08:18.065
[ CONVERSATIONS IN SPANISH ]

08:19.332 --> 08:21.001
Collins: WHAT IS THIS?

08:21.034 --> 08:22.202
DON'T LOOK AT ME.

08:22.235 --> 08:26.306
I'VE BEEN STUCK IN A CELL, SHOT,
AND TETHERED TO A DASHBOARD.

08:26.339 --> 08:28.141
[ HORN HONKING ]

08:28.175 --> 08:29.643
COME ON!

08:29.677 --> 08:31.579
LOOK, THOSE MANGOES
AREN'T GONNA MOVE THEMSELVES.

08:31.612 --> 08:33.046
I'M HAPPY TO LEND A HAND
IF YOU'D -- OW.

08:33.080 --> 08:35.082
[ ZIP TIE CLICKS ]
DON'T MAKE ME
SHOOT YOU AGAIN.

08:36.449 --> 08:38.351
[ CONVERSATIONS CONTINUE ]

08:38.385 --> 08:40.487
HEY!

08:40.520 --> 08:42.923
GET THAT CART
OUT OF THE ROAD!

08:45.192 --> 08:46.493
WHAT IS THIS?
áNDALE!

08:46.526 --> 08:48.261
[ CONVERSATION IN SPANISH ]

08:48.295 --> 08:50.530
EXCUSE ME, SIR, ARE YOU YELLING
AT THESE CHILDREN?

08:50.564 --> 08:52.099
STAY OUT OF IT.

08:52.132 --> 08:54.902
[ SPEAKING SPANISH ]

08:54.935 --> 08:56.503
Mozzie: YOU'RE NOT FROM HERE,
ARE YOU?

08:56.536 --> 08:57.838
WELL, SHOW SOME DECENCY.
HELP CLEAN IT UP.

08:57.871 --> 09:00.874
COME ON, LET'S GET THIS STUFF
OUT OF THE ROAD.

09:00.908 --> 09:02.509
COME ON.
I GOT A PLANE TO CATCH.

09:02.542 --> 09:03.944
[ HECTOR SPEAKING SPANISH ]

09:03.977 --> 09:07.915
I HOPE YOU'RE PLANNING ON PAYING
THIS KID FOR SO-- SIR!

09:07.948 --> 09:10.718
HERE, HELP ME
WITH THESE WATERMELONS.

09:14.722 --> 09:15.789
WHAT TOOK YOU SO LONG?

09:15.823 --> 09:16.924
GOT CAUGHT IN TRAFFIC.

09:16.957 --> 09:18.959
I GOT A CAR PARKED
A BLOCK FROM HERE.

09:18.992 --> 09:20.861
WE'RE GONNA HAVE
TO MOVE QUICK.

09:20.894 --> 09:22.529
YEAH,
QUICK MAY BE A PROBLEM.

09:22.562 --> 09:23.797
YOU'RE SHOT?

09:23.831 --> 09:26.967
OH, NEAL, I EXPECTED YOU
TO BE MOBILE.

09:27.000 --> 09:28.068
WELL,
COLLINS THOUGHT AHEAD.

09:28.101 --> 09:29.169
[ SIGHS ]
Collins: COME ON ALREADY!

09:32.606 --> 09:35.008
Mozzie: SIR, THERE'S A LOT
OF FRUIT HERE.

09:37.144 --> 09:38.746
AVOCADO.

09:38.779 --> 09:40.413
MAYBE I SHOULD CALL IT.
Collins: HEY, THERE'S STILL SOME
MANGOES BY THE TIRE.

09:40.447 --> 09:41.749
WHAT?

09:41.782 --> 09:43.717
NO. NO, I'M NOT
GOING BACK TO PRISON.

09:43.751 --> 09:44.885
LET'S GO.
YOU'RE OKAY?

09:44.918 --> 09:45.919
Yes!

09:45.953 --> 09:47.220
ALL RIGHT.
WHAT'S THE PLAN?

09:47.254 --> 09:49.056
THE MARINA --
I HAVE ACCESS TO A YACHT.

09:49.089 --> 09:51.291
I STOLE THE KEYS
TO DOBBS' BOAT.

09:51.324 --> 09:52.760
I DON'T THINK HE'LL MIND.

09:52.793 --> 09:54.227
WE'LL HAVE TO TEXT MOZZIE.

09:54.261 --> 09:56.897
HE HATES IT WHEN YOU DEVIATE
FROM THE PLAN.

09:56.930 --> 09:59.499
AND HE REALLY HATES IT
WHEN I DRIVE HIS CAR.

09:59.532 --> 10:01.134
ALL RIGHT, I'LL DRIVE.

10:01.168 --> 10:03.136
ALMOST DONE.

10:03.170 --> 10:05.072
[ GRUNTS ]
ALL RIGHT,
GET IT OFF THE ROAD!

10:05.105 --> 10:05.839
MOVE!

10:05.873 --> 10:07.941
[ INDISTINCT SHOUTING ]

10:10.443 --> 10:12.179
HEY! HEY, CAFFREY!

10:13.446 --> 10:14.782
CAFFREY!

10:16.283 --> 10:17.117
[ SIGHS ]

10:21.488 --> 10:23.691
HECTOR, MUY BIEN.

10:27.627 --> 10:30.097
Peter: DO YOU KNOW
WHICH ONE IS HIS?

10:30.130 --> 10:31.464
Neal: NOPE.

10:31.498 --> 10:33.100
YOU DITCHED ME.
YOU STOLE MY CAR.

10:33.133 --> 10:34.668
I HAD TO TAKE
A TAXI HERE.
SHH!

10:34.702 --> 10:35.803
THAT WAS NOT THE PLAN.

10:35.836 --> 10:37.771
WHAT HAPPENED TO YOU?
I GOT SHOT.

10:37.805 --> 10:39.272
OH.
WELCOME TO THE CLUB.

10:39.306 --> 10:40.607
IT'S GOOD TO BE A MEMBER.

10:40.640 --> 10:41.942
AND I'M FINE.
THANK YOU.

10:41.975 --> 10:43.476
WE NEED TO FIND
DOBBS' BOAT.

10:43.510 --> 10:45.979
OH, WELL, THE MIDDLE ONE DOESN'T
HAVE DEEP-SEA-FISHING MOUNTS,

10:46.013 --> 10:47.380
AND DOBBS WENT OUT
LAST WEEK.

10:47.414 --> 10:49.349
SCRATCH THE MIDDLE.

10:49.382 --> 10:52.319
THAT LEAVES US
ABOUT A DOZEN.

10:56.690 --> 10:58.792
THE MODEL BOATS
IN DOBBS' LIBRARY --

10:58.826 --> 11:00.360
THEY ALL HAD WOMEN'S NAMES.

11:00.393 --> 11:03.831
YEAH, THERE WAS, UM, CLAUDIA,
ANNETTE, ADELE...

11:03.864 --> 11:06.633
ESMERELDA, ISABELLA...

11:06.666 --> 11:10.570
* ISABELLA, I CAN TELL-A

11:10.603 --> 11:13.306
* ESMERELDA,
FIND ADELE-A *

11:13.340 --> 11:14.674
PETER,
THIS IS NOT THE TIME.
WHAT?

11:14.708 --> 11:16.710
* MIRABELLA, SO COMPELLA

11:16.744 --> 11:18.145
WAS THERE A MIRABELLA?

11:18.178 --> 11:19.046
YEAH.

11:19.079 --> 11:21.481
* ROB'S FAIR LADIES

11:21.514 --> 11:22.415
DID HE GET
INTO THE RUM?

11:22.449 --> 11:23.516
I DON'T KNOW.

11:23.550 --> 11:25.085
THESE WERE THE NAMES
OF DOBBS' BOATS?

11:25.118 --> 11:26.486
YEAH.
HOW'D YOU KNOW THAT?

11:26.519 --> 11:28.555
WHO CARES? WHY DID YOU JUST
DEFILE A NURSERY RHYME?

11:28.588 --> 11:31.091
FORGET THE BOAT.

11:31.124 --> 11:34.361
I THINK I HAVE A WAY
TO GET YOU BACK TO NEW YORK.

11:42.970 --> 11:45.505
I'M TELLING YOU,
IT'S ROBERT MACLEISH.

11:45.538 --> 11:46.907
OH, COME ON, PETER.

11:46.940 --> 11:49.409
YOU SPOT A FEW BOAT NAMES
AND YOU EXPECT ME TO BELIEVE --

11:49.442 --> 11:51.078
I KNOW IT SOUNDS CRAZY.

11:51.111 --> 11:52.445
WELL, YOU'RE DAMN RIGHT
IT DOES.

11:52.479 --> 11:54.347
MACLEISH HAS BEEN AT THE TOP
OF THE MOST WANTED FOR 20 YEARS,

11:54.381 --> 11:55.849
AND IN ALL THAT TIME,
NO ONE'S SEEN HIM.

11:55.883 --> 11:57.417
BECAUSE HE'S BEEN HERE --

11:57.450 --> 12:00.453
ON AN ISLAND OFF THE RADAR
WITH NO EXTRADITION.

12:00.487 --> 12:02.522
I'M LOOKING
AT CAFFREY'S SKETCH.

12:02.555 --> 12:06.459
IT LOOKS AS MUCH LIKE MACLEISH
AS MY COUSIN PHYLLIS.

12:08.796 --> 12:11.364
BECAUSE HE'S HAD MAJOR
RECONSTRUCTIVE SURGERY.

12:11.398 --> 12:13.901
LISTEN TO YOURSELF.
YOU'RE NOT THIS MAN, PETER.

12:13.934 --> 12:16.269
YOU'RE GRASPING AT STRAWS,
AND YOU KNOW IT.

12:16.303 --> 12:17.905
HE'S HERE, REESE.

12:17.938 --> 12:20.540
YEAH, WELL, YOU'RE GONNA HAVE
TO GIVE ME MORE TO GO ON

12:20.573 --> 12:21.775
THAN A FEW WOMEN'S NAMES.

12:21.809 --> 12:23.210
HEY, PETER,
IF YOU CAN GET US A PHOTO,

12:23.243 --> 12:24.644
WE CAN RUN IT
THROUGH BIOMETRICS.

12:24.677 --> 12:25.946
WORKING ON THAT NOW.

12:25.979 --> 12:27.214
BUT ASSUMING IT'S HIM --

12:27.247 --> 12:29.049
Well,
that's a big assumption.

12:29.082 --> 12:32.385
IF IT'S HIM,
WHAT IS HE WORTH TO THE BUREAU?

12:32.419 --> 12:34.988
WHAT ARE YOU SUGGESTING?

12:35.022 --> 12:37.590
IF CAFFREY CATCHES HIM --
CAFFREY?!

12:37.624 --> 12:39.392
Yes.
If Caffrey catches him

12:39.426 --> 12:41.061
and delivers him to you,

12:41.094 --> 12:44.431
WOULD JUSTICE AGREE TO LET HIM
RETURN TO NEW YORK

12:44.464 --> 12:46.266
AND REINSTATE
HIS OLD DEAL?

12:46.299 --> 12:47.835
Back on his anklet,
working cases?

12:47.868 --> 12:50.337
YES. WORKING FOR ME.

12:50.370 --> 12:52.772
Oh, my God. Well,
that's a hell of a tall order.

12:52.806 --> 12:54.741
I KNOW.

12:54.774 --> 12:57.644
FIRST,
PROVE IT'S MACLEISH.

12:57.677 --> 13:00.647
If it's him,
I'll run it by Justice,

13:00.680 --> 13:01.982
BUT NO PROMISES.

13:02.015 --> 13:03.650
Yes!

13:03.683 --> 13:05.318
THANKS, REESE.

13:05.352 --> 13:08.822
AND, PETER, NEXT TIME,
TAKE ME OFF SPEAKER.

13:09.890 --> 13:11.524
[ TELEPHONE BEEPS ]

13:11.558 --> 13:13.426
I DIDN'T THINK
HE'D GO FOR IT.

13:13.460 --> 13:14.661
YEAH. WELL...

13:14.694 --> 13:17.164
I GOT A PROMISE
ON A MAYBE.

13:17.197 --> 13:19.466
BUT YOU'RE GIVING ME
A CHANCE.

13:19.499 --> 13:21.501
[ KNOCKS ON TABLE ]

13:23.971 --> 13:26.373
MOZ, YOU GET THE PHOTOS
OF DOBBS?

13:26.406 --> 13:27.207
UPLOADING.
[ BEEP ]

13:27.240 --> 13:30.277
* ISABELLA, I CAN TELL-A

13:30.310 --> 13:32.946
* ESMERELDA, FIND ADELE-A
STAYS IN YOUR HEAD.

13:32.980 --> 13:34.114
IT'S DRIVING ME INSANE!

13:34.147 --> 13:36.783
WAS THIS LIKE
SOME GOVERNMENT EXPERIMENT

13:36.816 --> 13:38.285
IN TUNE IMPLANTATION?

13:38.318 --> 13:41.788
MACLEISH IS A REQUIRED
FIRST-YEAR CASE AT QUANTICO.

13:41.821 --> 13:43.390
THE FBI PURSUED HIM

13:43.423 --> 13:45.692
THROUGH A LIST OF MANY WOMEN
IN HIS LIFE.

13:45.725 --> 13:48.161
THE NAMES OF THESE WOMEN
WERE ON A TEST.

13:48.195 --> 13:51.031
THE SONG'S A MNEMONIC DEVICE
TO REMEMBER THE NAMES.

13:51.064 --> 13:52.866
BUT THE FBI
NEVER FOUND HIM.

13:52.900 --> 13:55.635
SO IT'S LIKE AN EXERCISE
IN HARMONIC FUTILITY,

13:55.668 --> 13:57.137
MUCH LIKE "THE MACARENA."

13:57.170 --> 13:59.639
YEAH, WELL,
WE CAME CLOSE WITH MIRABELLA,

13:59.672 --> 14:00.640
BUT HE WISED UP.

14:00.673 --> 14:01.708
OR SO YOU THOUGHT.

14:01.741 --> 14:03.010
YEAH.

14:03.043 --> 14:06.079
THE GIRL ALWAYS
GIVES YOU AWAY.

14:18.291 --> 14:20.994
FEELS A LITTLE LONG
FOR BIOMETRICS.

14:21.028 --> 14:22.562
A LITTLE TOO LONG.

14:24.965 --> 14:27.700
BEFORE WE TAKE
THIS FURTHER, SUIT,

14:27.734 --> 14:30.003
I NEED TO CLEAR
THE AIR HERE.

14:30.037 --> 14:31.404
MOZ --
I-I-I KNOW.

14:31.438 --> 14:33.907
BUT HE TRAVELED
HALFWAY AROUND THE WORLD

14:33.941 --> 14:37.444
ON AN UNSANCTIONED MANHUNT
TO TRACK US DOWN.

14:37.477 --> 14:39.679
AND NOW HE'S TRYING TO MOVE
HEAVEN AND EARTH

14:39.712 --> 14:41.114
TO BRING YOU BACK
TO NEW YORK.

14:41.148 --> 14:44.051
I THINK WE DESERVE
TO KNOW WHY.

14:46.286 --> 14:47.354
[ SIGHS ]

14:47.387 --> 14:50.290
I SUSPECTED YOU HAVING THE ART
FROM THE U-BOAT,

14:50.323 --> 14:52.960
AND I BROUGHT IN KRAMER
TO HELP ME PROVE IT.

14:52.993 --> 14:54.194
YOU HAD EVERY RIGHT TO.

14:54.227 --> 14:56.729
I KNOW. I DID.
BUT...

14:56.763 --> 14:58.932
KRAMER CROSSED THE LINE.

14:58.966 --> 15:01.201
HE CROSSED THE LINE, PETER.
YOU DIDN'T.

15:01.234 --> 15:04.404
NEAL,
YOU'LL BE RUNNING FOREVER.

15:06.806 --> 15:09.442
BUT BRINGING HOME
MACLEISH --

15:09.476 --> 15:13.113
THIS IS A WAY
TO SET THINGS RIGHT.

15:14.747 --> 15:17.617
[ CELL PHONE BUZZES ]

15:19.686 --> 15:20.988
[ BEEP ]

15:21.021 --> 15:23.423
THIS IS PETER BURKE.

15:30.663 --> 15:32.265
YES.

15:35.002 --> 15:36.469
THANK YOU.

15:36.503 --> 15:38.071
[ CELL PHONE BEEPS ]

15:38.105 --> 15:40.940
BIOMETRICS MATCHED.
IT'S MACLEISH.

15:40.974 --> 15:42.909
HOW DO WE GET HIM
BACK TO THE U.S.?

15:42.942 --> 15:45.078
WITHOUT A LOT OF HELP
FROM HOPALONG HERE.

15:45.112 --> 15:47.514
AND CONSIDERING YOU DON'T HAVE
THE POWER TO EXTRADITE...

15:47.547 --> 15:49.249
AND YOU HAVE A TARGET
ON YOUR BACK...

15:49.282 --> 15:51.451
AND YOU CAN'T MAKE AN ARREST
OR CARRY A WEAPON...

15:51.484 --> 15:53.286
OKAY, YOU'RE BOTH
EQUALLY IMPOTENT.

15:53.320 --> 15:56.956
BUT...WE STILL HAVE OPTIONS.

15:57.857 --> 16:01.528
IF DOBBS' POWER COMES FROM
PAYING OFF LOCAL AUTHORITIES,

16:01.561 --> 16:02.929
WHAT IF THAT GOES AWAY?

16:02.962 --> 16:04.331
AND HE CAN'T PAY THEM OFF?

16:04.364 --> 16:05.832
WE STEAL BACK
THE BRIBE MONEY.

16:05.865 --> 16:08.401
WE LET THE WORD SPREAD THAT HE'S
SKIPPING TOWN WITH THE CASH.

16:09.802 --> 16:11.138
HIS PARTY.

16:11.171 --> 16:13.973
YES! EVERYONE HE'S PAYING OFF
WILL BE THERE.

16:14.007 --> 16:16.043
THEY FIND OUT
THAT HE'S LEAVING TOWN...

16:16.076 --> 16:18.545
DROP IN A FEW KEY WHISPERS,
SOME DAMNING EVIDENCE...

16:18.578 --> 16:22.582
I THINK WE HAVE A PLAN.

16:24.884 --> 16:26.286
Neal:
THIS IS SHERIFF MORALES.

16:26.319 --> 16:28.455
HE'S A TALKER, AND HIS WORD
CARRIES A LOT OF WEIGHT.

16:28.488 --> 16:31.058
THEN HE'S A GOOD PERSON
TO START HEARING SOME WHISPERS.

16:31.091 --> 16:32.959
HE SPENDS A LOT OF TIME
AT THE MARINA.

16:32.992 --> 16:34.994
GREAT. AND HE SHOULD SEE
SOMEONE FUELING

16:35.028 --> 16:36.563
DOBBS' BOAT
FOR A LONG VOYAGE.

16:36.596 --> 16:38.465
HERE ARE THE KEYS
TO THE ESMERELDA.

16:38.498 --> 16:41.801
GAS HER UP AND PUT ANOTHER
50 GALLONS IN THE CABIN.

16:41.834 --> 16:43.303
WHERE IS MR. DOBBS' GOING?

16:43.336 --> 16:46.506
FAR.
THAT'S ALL I KNOW.

16:49.109 --> 16:51.378
PETER, THE PARTY --
HOW ARE YOUR MIXOLOGY SKILLS?

16:51.411 --> 16:52.845
YOU WANT ME TO TEND BAR?

16:52.879 --> 16:54.514
EVERYBODY TALKS
TO THE BARTENDER.

16:54.547 --> 16:56.416
I TAPPED A KEG OR TWO
IN COLLEGE.

16:56.449 --> 16:59.018
HMM.
I'LL GIVE YOU A REFRESHER.

16:59.052 --> 17:00.553
DON'T FORGET YOUR GARNISH,
OKAY?

17:00.587 --> 17:01.921
THAT'S JUST AS IMPORTANT
AS THE POUR.

17:01.954 --> 17:03.256
YEP. YEP.

17:03.290 --> 17:04.324
YOU KNOW,
BEFORE YOU POUR,

17:04.357 --> 17:05.892
ADD A LITTLE FLOURISH TO IT,
YOU KNOW?

17:05.925 --> 17:07.194
SPIN IT AROUND,
THROW IT IN THE AIR.

17:07.227 --> 17:09.562
THAT'S GOOD.
GO BACK TO
YOUR BASEBALL DAYS.

17:09.596 --> 17:11.431
BASEBALL.
NICE.

17:11.464 --> 17:14.000
YEAH, THAT'S --
WE CAN WORK ON THAT.

17:14.033 --> 17:15.368
YEAH.
FOR SURE.

17:15.402 --> 17:17.504
ALL RIGHT, BUT WHAT ABOUT
HIS REGULAR BARTENDER?

17:17.537 --> 17:20.173
OH, HE MAY HAVE WON AN
ALL-EXPENSE-PAID DREAM VACATION

17:20.207 --> 17:21.674
THAT TAKES PLACE
THE DAY OF THE PARTY.

17:21.708 --> 17:22.875
IT COULD WORK,

17:22.909 --> 17:25.412
BUT HE'S NOT GONNA HIRE ME
BECAUSE OF MY PRETTY FACE.

17:25.445 --> 17:27.347
NO.

17:27.380 --> 17:29.216
BUT IF YOU GOT
A RECOMMENDATION

17:29.249 --> 17:31.518
FROM ONE OF THE ISLAND'S
TOP CATERERS...

17:31.551 --> 17:32.752
MAYA?

17:32.785 --> 17:35.455
NO. I DON'T WANT HER INVOLVED
IN THIS, MOZ.

17:35.488 --> 17:37.124
WHAT IF SHE'S
WILLING TO HELP?

17:37.157 --> 17:38.291
YOU TALKED TO HER?

17:38.325 --> 17:39.792
SHE'S WORRIED ABOUT YOU.

17:39.826 --> 17:42.762
AND I'M SURE SHE'LL GIVE PETER
A GLOWING RECOMMENDATION.

17:57.310 --> 18:01.581
Maya: NEAL, THIS PLAN
SOUNDS INCREDIBLY INTRICATE.

18:01.614 --> 18:03.416
IT IS.

18:03.450 --> 18:05.118
WHAT HAPPENS
IF IT DOESN'T WORK?

18:06.619 --> 18:08.221
IT WILL.

18:08.255 --> 18:10.257
WHAT IF YOU GET CAUGHT?

18:10.290 --> 18:12.892
WELL, THEN I GO TO JAIL

18:12.925 --> 18:15.895
FOR A LONG, LONG TIME.

18:15.928 --> 18:17.930
OR WORSE.

18:17.964 --> 18:21.568
WE'RE GONNA STAY
A STEP AHEAD OF HIM.

18:21.601 --> 18:23.503
I WOULDN'T HAVE ASKED
FOR YOUR HELP

18:23.536 --> 18:25.305
UNLESS I KNEW
IT WOULD WORK.

18:25.338 --> 18:29.108
YOU REALLY THINK DOBBS
WILL LEAVE THE ISLAND FOR GOOD?

18:29.142 --> 18:31.711
THAT'S WHAT YOU WANT,
ISN'T IT?

18:46.526 --> 18:50.363
THAT WASN'T THE ONLY THING
ON MY LIST.

18:59.972 --> 19:01.941
WE'LL MAKE IT HAPPEN.

19:01.974 --> 19:03.643
[ CHUCKLES SOFTLY ]

19:03.676 --> 19:06.646
I HOPE YOUR FRIEND
IS A GOOD BARTENDER.

19:12.752 --> 19:16.489
NEAL, DO WE HAVE BITTERS?

19:16.523 --> 19:17.824
NICE.

19:17.857 --> 19:18.791
YEAH, YOU'LL GET IT.

19:18.825 --> 19:19.826
YEAH.

19:19.859 --> 19:21.494
HERE YOU GO, MOZ.

19:29.536 --> 19:31.804
IF YOU CAN'T NAIL
THE QUALITY,

19:31.838 --> 19:33.373
GO FOR QUANTITY.

19:33.406 --> 19:34.841
HE'S WORKING ON IT.
ALL RIGHT.

19:34.874 --> 19:37.176
NO, GIN.
RIGHT.

19:37.210 --> 19:40.847
YEAH, POUR IT LIKE
IT'S HEMINGWAY'S LAST CALL.

19:42.382 --> 19:45.352
SO, THAT'S THE EQUIPMENT
TO OPEN A SAFE?

19:45.385 --> 19:48.888
YEAH. BACK TO WHY A GENEROUS
POUR IS SO IMPORTANT --

19:48.921 --> 19:50.690
HE'S GOT A BRICKMAN 2-5-10.

19:50.723 --> 19:53.192
YOU CAN'T CRACK THAT,
CAN YOU?
NO.

19:53.226 --> 19:54.994
NO, NOT WITHOUT
HEAVY EQUIPMENT

19:55.027 --> 19:56.563
AND SEVERAL HOURS
OF ALONE TIME.

19:56.596 --> 19:58.531
YOU'RE GONNA HAVE MINUTES,
AT BEST.

19:58.565 --> 20:00.700
LOOK, ALL THE DRUNKEN WHISPERS
IN THE WORLD WON'T MATTER

20:00.733 --> 20:02.402
IF IT DOESN'T LOOK LIKE
HE'S MADE OFF

20:02.435 --> 20:03.570
WITH THEIR BRIBE MONEY.

20:03.603 --> 20:04.537
TRUE.

20:04.571 --> 20:05.738
SO, HOW YOU
GONNA OPEN THE SAFE

20:05.772 --> 20:06.939
AND HAVE IT EMPTY?

20:06.973 --> 20:09.175
WELL, WE DO
THE NEXT BEST THING.

20:09.208 --> 20:10.910
WHAT, FAKE AND BAKE?

20:10.943 --> 20:12.345
WHAT'S A FAKE AND BAKE?

20:12.379 --> 20:15.415
WE'LL MAKE IT LOOK LIKE
IT'S EMPTY.

20:16.883 --> 20:20.520
[ DRILLING ]

20:20.553 --> 20:22.555
THIS FRAME IS LARGER
THAN I EXPECTED.

20:22.589 --> 20:25.425
WE'LL NEED TO FIND A WAY TO
SNEAK IT INTO DOBBS' LIBRARY

20:25.458 --> 20:26.426
DURING THE PARTY.

20:26.459 --> 20:30.297
HOW'S HECTOR'S AIM?

20:48.080 --> 20:48.915
[ GLASS SHATTERS ]

20:52.819 --> 20:54.287
Peter: GENTLEMEN...

21:02.995 --> 21:04.731
TO THE ISLAND'S
MOST WANTED.

21:04.764 --> 21:07.600
MAY THEY BE RETURNED
TO WHERE THEY BELONG.

21:12.639 --> 21:13.973
THAT'S NOT AN OMEN.

21:14.006 --> 21:15.241
NO.

21:15.274 --> 21:17.610
NO.

21:32.191 --> 21:33.893
COME OUT WITH YOUR HANDS UP!

21:35.962 --> 21:37.830
YOU'RE TOO LATE.

21:37.864 --> 21:38.998
DO YOU MIND?

21:39.031 --> 21:41.200
GO, GO.

21:41.233 --> 21:43.336
BURKE, IS HE HERE?

21:43.370 --> 21:46.339
YOU TELL ME.
I'M DONE.

21:46.373 --> 21:48.441
WHAT DO YOU MEAN
YOU'RE DONE?

21:48.475 --> 21:51.277
I CAME HERE TO CONVINCE NEAL
TO TURN HIMSELF IN.

21:51.310 --> 21:53.346
MEANWHILE,
YOU GOT THE WILD BUNCH

21:53.380 --> 21:55.882
CHASING HIM DOWN LIKE A DOG
ON THE STREET.

21:55.915 --> 21:57.016
I'M DOING MY JOB.

21:57.049 --> 21:58.485
REALLY?

21:58.518 --> 22:00.286
WORD AROUND TOWN
IS THAT YOU SHOT HIM.

22:00.319 --> 22:01.554
[ CHUCKLES ]

22:01.588 --> 22:03.990
YOU'RE A BIGGER MENACE TO
SOCIETY THAN HE EVER WAS.

22:04.023 --> 22:06.659
YEAH, WELL, PLAYING BY YOUR BOOK
ONLY GETS YOU SO FAR.

22:06.693 --> 22:09.462
WHICH IS WHY I BOOKED
A 4:00 FLIGHT OUT OF HERE.

22:09.496 --> 22:13.900
I'M A WHITE-COLLAR AGENT,
NOT A BOUNTY HUNTER.

22:13.933 --> 22:15.702
[ GLASS THUDS ]

22:15.735 --> 22:18.237
BESIDES,
I'M OUT OF VACATION DAYS.

22:18.270 --> 22:21.474
IT'S ALL YOURS NOW!

22:21.508 --> 22:23.543
THE BAR'S OPEN.

22:26.245 --> 22:27.680
[ SCOFFS ]

22:33.953 --> 22:37.256
* WEEKENDS LOOK UP
FROM THE GROUND *

22:37.289 --> 22:41.861
* IS THIS MY SOPHOMORE SOUND?

22:41.894 --> 22:46.365
* AND COME KEEP BREATHING, TELL
ME, OH, JUST WHAT YOU WANT *

22:46.399 --> 22:47.900
* YEAH

22:47.934 --> 22:51.203
* IT'S JUST I FEEL,
IT'S JUST I FEEL OKAY *

22:51.237 --> 22:54.907
* IT'S HOW I DO,
IT'S HOW I DO WHEN YOU'RE AWAY *

22:54.941 --> 22:58.711
* BUT DON'T TELL, DON'T TELL,
I'M OKAY *

23:01.313 --> 23:03.883
[ SOFT MUSIC PLAYING ]

23:03.916 --> 23:05.017
Peter: BUENOS DíAS.

23:05.051 --> 23:06.185
Woman: APPLETINI.

23:06.218 --> 23:09.021
APPLETINI.
COMING RIGHT UP.

23:09.055 --> 23:10.857
THIS IS A BEAUTIFUL PARTY.

23:10.890 --> 23:14.393
YES. WELL, MR. DOBBS KNOWS HOW
TO DO IT RIGHT, DOESN'T HE?

23:14.427 --> 23:16.095
WHERE'S RAJULIO?

23:16.128 --> 23:18.097
OH, SO SAD.

23:18.130 --> 23:20.533
RAJULIO --
HE HAS BEEN DETAINED

23:20.567 --> 23:22.635
BY THE AMERICAN
FEDERAL AGENT.

23:22.669 --> 23:24.704
OH.

23:24.737 --> 23:25.872
MM-HMM.

23:25.905 --> 23:28.307
I'M KEVIN.

23:28.340 --> 23:29.576
THANK YOU.

23:31.410 --> 23:33.646
DID YOU KNOW
THAT RAJULIO'S NOT HERE

23:33.680 --> 23:36.015
BECAUSE HE'S BEEN DETAINED
BY THE FEDS?

23:39.251 --> 23:40.620
Man: NO, NO, NO, NO.

23:40.653 --> 23:42.555
NO, YOU'RE NOT SUPPOSED
TO BE HERE UNTIL TOMORROW.

23:42.589 --> 23:44.757
IT'S MR. DOBBS.
WE RUSHED THE ORDER.

23:44.791 --> 23:46.759
YOU WANT TO GIVE ME
A HAND HERE?

23:46.793 --> 23:48.227
THERE MUST BE SOME TYPE
OF MIX-UP.

23:48.260 --> 23:49.562
MR. DOBBS IS
ENTERTAINING TONIGHT.

23:49.596 --> 23:51.564
OH, HE'S HAVING A PARTY?
NO PROBLEMO.
YES.

23:51.598 --> 23:54.000
I'LL FIX HIS WINDOW
BEFORE A GUEST EVEN NOTICES.

23:54.033 --> 23:56.903
Mozzie: HEY, HEY, HEY!
EYES ON THE JOB.

23:56.936 --> 23:58.270
YOU WANT TO EXPLAIN
TO YOUR BOSS

23:58.304 --> 23:59.772
WHY HE HAS TO PAY
FOR THIS TWICE?

24:07.346 --> 24:08.681
[ GRUNTS ]

24:14.353 --> 24:17.624
Mozzie:
THIS WINDOW CRATE IS HEAVY.

24:17.657 --> 24:20.092
NO ONE TOLD ME
THERE'S A SECOND FLOOR.

24:20.126 --> 24:24.497
HERE,
L-LIFT FROM THE KNEES, MUCHACHO.

24:24.531 --> 24:26.499
I'M CONCERNED ABOUT YOUR BACK.

24:26.533 --> 24:28.968
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

24:29.001 --> 24:29.969
AH.

24:30.002 --> 24:32.304
THANK YOU.

24:32.338 --> 24:33.472
[ CONVERSATION IN SPANISH ]

24:33.506 --> 24:35.141
POR FAVOR.

24:42.148 --> 24:44.450
CUBA LIBRE.

24:44.483 --> 24:46.452
CUBA LIBRE.
VERY GOOD.

24:46.485 --> 24:48.721
WHAT IS THIS
ABOUT RAJULIO?

24:48.755 --> 24:50.523
UH, I DON'T WANT
TO GET HIM IN TROUBLE.

24:50.557 --> 24:52.458
HE'S NOT.

24:52.491 --> 24:54.060
THE AMERICANS
DETAINED HIM, RIGHT?

24:55.695 --> 24:57.930
I'M GUESSING IT'S BECAUSE
OF ALL THAT CASH.

24:59.165 --> 25:00.800
RAJULIO SAW THEM LOADING

25:00.833 --> 25:03.903
ALL THE MONEY OUT OF THE SAFE
INTO MR. DOBBS' BOAT.

25:03.936 --> 25:07.473
WELL,
THAT'S WHAT HE SAID.

25:07.506 --> 25:09.576
I-I DON'T KNOW.
WHAT CAN I GET YOU?

25:09.609 --> 25:11.010
WHISKEY, PLEASE.

25:18.184 --> 25:19.518
SALUD.

25:19.552 --> 25:20.753
SALUD, SIR.

25:20.787 --> 25:22.154
Man:
SOMETHING'S WRONG.

25:22.188 --> 25:23.923
Rajulio saw Dobbs' cash.

25:23.956 --> 25:26.525
WOMAN:
What's Dobbs doing with it?

25:38.137 --> 25:39.972
CLEAR?
CLEAR.

25:48.214 --> 25:50.116
LET'S SEE HERE.

25:54.954 --> 25:56.756
HMM.
GOING ISLAND HOPPING?

25:56.789 --> 25:58.691
EH, YOU BEEN SAVING
THAT ONE?

25:58.725 --> 25:59.892
NOPE.
JUST CAME TO ME.

26:03.262 --> 26:05.131
ALL RIGHT.
WE BETTER HURRY.

26:09.669 --> 26:12.071
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

26:41.934 --> 26:44.203
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS
CONTINUE ]

26:46.806 --> 26:49.942
EXCUSE ME FOR A MINUTE.

26:49.976 --> 26:53.312
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS
CONTINUE ]

26:56.548 --> 26:59.018
ALL RIGHT,
HOW DOES THAT LOOK?

26:59.051 --> 27:00.152
UH, PRETTY GOOD.

27:00.186 --> 27:02.789
TAKE A LOOK AT THE DOOR,
WILL YOU?

27:06.158 --> 27:07.426
ALL RIGHT.

27:07.459 --> 27:08.594
OH, JUST REMEMBER --

27:08.627 --> 27:10.663
DOBBS IS ABOUT
3 INCHES TALLER THAN I AM.

27:10.697 --> 27:12.498
YEAH, AND THE SHERIFF'S
ABOUT AN INCH SHORTER.

27:12.531 --> 27:13.599
LET'S SPLIT THE DIFFERENCE.

27:13.632 --> 27:16.335
[ WIND BLOWING,
WINDOWS CLATTERING ]

27:30.082 --> 27:32.351
ANY CHANCE WE CAN REALLY
BREAK INTO THE SAFE

27:32.384 --> 27:34.954
AND STEAL THE MONEY
IN THE NEXT FIVE MINUTES?

27:34.987 --> 27:37.824
NO.

27:37.857 --> 27:40.827
NO, BUT THERE'S A STORAGE ROOM
NEXT DOOR.

27:40.860 --> 27:42.194
I JUST SAW IT ON THE WAY UP.
LET'S GO.

27:42.228 --> 27:43.229
OH, GREAT.

27:55.708 --> 27:57.176
GRACIAS.

27:58.677 --> 28:00.579
HE DIDN'T LEAVE.
[ SIGHS ]

28:00.612 --> 28:02.681
AND YOU WERE IN CONTACT
WITH HIM,

28:02.715 --> 28:04.817
SO YOU KNOW
EXACTLY WHERE HE IS.

28:04.851 --> 28:06.886
ARE YOU GOING
TO ORDER SOMETHING?

28:06.919 --> 28:08.187
YOU DO OKAY HERE --

28:08.220 --> 28:10.156
I MEAN, FOR A WOMAN
WHO'S ON HER OWN.

28:10.189 --> 28:12.658
I MEAN, THE FOOD IS DECENT.
THE SERVICE IS COURTEOUS.

28:12.691 --> 28:15.394
BUT YOU COULD REALLY USE
SOME UPGRADES.

28:15.427 --> 28:18.030
I MEAN, WHEN WAS THE LAST TIME
YOU BOUGHT SOME NEW GLASSWARE?

28:18.064 --> 28:20.432
HELL, WHEN WAS THE LAST TIME
YOU THOUGHT ABOUT REMODELING?

28:20.466 --> 28:22.101
WHY WOULD I REMODEL?

28:22.134 --> 28:23.870
BECAUSE THAT'S WHAT
PEOPLE DO

28:23.903 --> 28:26.138
WHEN THEY COME INTO
HALF A MILLION DOLLARS.

28:29.108 --> 28:31.710
THIS ISN'T A GOOD TIME
TO TALK.

28:34.881 --> 28:38.050
WELL, WHETHER IT'S TODAY
OR TOMORROW,

28:38.084 --> 28:40.086
NEAL CAFFREY
WILL LEAVE YOU.

28:40.119 --> 28:42.121
HE HA TO.
HE'S ON THE RUN.

28:42.154 --> 28:43.022
HE'S BAD NEWS.

28:43.055 --> 28:45.224
AND I WANT TO
GIVE YOU A CHANCE

28:45.257 --> 28:46.458
TO SAY WHEN IT ENDS,

28:46.492 --> 28:48.160
INSTEAD OF HIM.

28:54.266 --> 28:56.468
$500,000 U.S.

28:56.502 --> 28:58.905
TODAY, IF I CAPTURE HIM.

28:58.938 --> 29:01.607
BUT TOMORROW,
IF HE'S ALREADY GONE,

29:01.640 --> 29:04.076
THAT INFORMATION
IS WORTH NOTHING.

29:10.950 --> 29:13.185
I KNOW WHERE HE IS.

29:17.289 --> 29:19.558
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS
CONTINUE ]

29:19.591 --> 29:21.227
WOMAN:
What's Dobbs doing with it?

29:21.260 --> 29:23.963
AH, MR. DOBBS,
WHEN DO YOU LEAVE ON VACATION?

29:23.996 --> 29:26.398
I DON'T.
WHO SAYS I DID?

29:26.432 --> 29:27.566
OH, MY APOLOGIES, SIR.

29:27.599 --> 29:29.001
I DON'T REMEMBER HIS NAME,

29:29.035 --> 29:31.170
BUT HE SAID YOU HAD
THE ESMERELDA

29:31.203 --> 29:32.671
ALL GASSED UP
FOR A LONG TRIP.

29:32.704 --> 29:33.772
AGAIN, I-I'M SORRY.

29:33.806 --> 29:35.407
WHAT CAN I GET YOU?

29:35.441 --> 29:36.943
HORCHATA PONCHE.

29:36.976 --> 29:38.410
WHAT'S YOUR NAME?

29:38.444 --> 29:39.611
KEVIN, SIR.

29:39.645 --> 29:40.746
KEVIN?
YES.

29:40.779 --> 29:42.281
FIRST OF ALL, SHUT UP.

29:44.016 --> 29:46.118
SECOND,
I'M NOT GOING ANYWHERE.

29:46.152 --> 29:47.186
AND THIRD...

29:47.219 --> 29:49.621
THE ESMERELDA
IS NO ALL GASSED UP.

29:49.655 --> 29:51.257
HENRY, I WAS AT THE DOCKS

29:51.290 --> 29:53.659
WHEN THEY FUELED UP
THE ESMERELDA.

29:53.692 --> 29:54.626
[ Scoffing ] NO.

29:54.660 --> 29:55.862
YES.

29:55.895 --> 29:57.830
AND DON'T BE SO HARD
ON KEVIN, HERE.

29:57.864 --> 29:59.331
HE'S FILLING IN
FOR RAJULIO.

29:59.365 --> 30:00.266
WHO'S RAJULIO?

30:00.299 --> 30:03.202
RAJULIO IS
YOUR REGULAR BARTENDER.

30:03.235 --> 30:04.937
HE'S BEING QUESTIONED
BY THE FEDS RIGHT NOW.

30:04.971 --> 30:06.138
ABOUT YOU.

30:06.172 --> 30:07.840
WHOA, WHOA,
WHOA, WHOA, WHOA.

30:07.874 --> 30:09.208
THIS DOESN'T MAKE ANY SENSE.

30:09.241 --> 30:11.277
WHY WOULD THEY TALK
TO MY BARTENDER?

30:11.310 --> 30:14.646
BECAUSE HE SAW YOU LOADING BAGS
OF MONEY ONTO YOUR BOAT.

30:14.680 --> 30:16.448
WHAT?

30:16.482 --> 30:18.784
YOU'RE OUT OF YOUR MIND.

30:18.817 --> 30:20.219
Morales: OKAY.
LET ME GET THIS STRAIGHT.

30:20.252 --> 30:21.988
THE AMERICANS
ARE LOOKING INTO YOU,

30:22.021 --> 30:24.156
YOU GASSED UP YOUR BOAT,
AND YOU LOADED IT WITH CASH?

30:24.190 --> 30:25.892
NOTHING YOU'VE SAID IS TRUE.

30:25.925 --> 30:27.459
EXCEPT I WAS AT THE MARINA!

30:27.493 --> 30:29.795
I SAW THEM FUELING UP
THE ESMERELDA.

30:29.828 --> 30:31.297
ALL RIGHT.

30:31.330 --> 30:33.900
YOUR MONEY IS WHERE
IT'S ALWAYS BEEN,

30:33.933 --> 30:36.702
AND I'M NOT
GOING ANYWHERE.

30:36.735 --> 30:38.804
OKAY. PROVE IT.

30:38.837 --> 30:41.240
OKAY.

30:59.558 --> 31:01.560
[ PEN CLICKS, CLATTERS ]

31:04.696 --> 31:06.532
YOU WORK FOR MR. DOBBS,
RIGHT?

31:06.565 --> 31:10.002
LISTEN, IF THINGS GET BAD
FOR YOUR BOSS IN THERE,

31:10.036 --> 31:12.604
I HEARD THAT ONE
OF DOBBS' FRIENDS

31:12.638 --> 31:14.873
HAD A PLANE LEAVING
THE AIRPORT.

31:14.907 --> 31:16.075
YOU KNOW.

31:20.746 --> 31:23.349
[ CELL PHONE BUZZES ]

31:23.382 --> 31:24.383
[ BEEP ]

31:24.416 --> 31:25.751
PETER?

31:25.784 --> 31:27.319
SHOWTIME.

31:30.089 --> 31:33.359
NOW, THIS ISN'T EXACTLY
HOW WE PLANNED OUR RETIREMENT.

31:33.392 --> 31:36.195
NEAL, THE LAW ON OUR TAIL,
AN OCEAN BREEZE,

31:36.228 --> 31:38.864
A PRECISION HEIST
FROM AN ISLAND OVERLORD.

31:38.897 --> 31:40.066
IT KIND OF IS.

31:41.233 --> 31:43.135
Dobbs: YOU HAVE NOTHING
TO WORRY ABOUT.

31:44.436 --> 31:46.638
AS YOU --

31:52.678 --> 31:54.213
WAIT, WAIT.

31:54.246 --> 31:56.115
WAIT, WAIT.
I DIDN'T DO THIS.

31:56.148 --> 31:57.416
YOU SON OF A BITCH.

31:57.449 --> 32:00.052
YOU'RE TRYING TO SKIP TOWN
WITH OUR MONEY!

32:00.086 --> 32:01.120
NO, NO, NO, NO.

32:01.153 --> 32:03.089
LOOK,
I-I-I'LL GIVE YOU MONEY.

32:03.122 --> 32:04.723
I'LL GIVE YOU MORE MONEY.

32:04.756 --> 32:06.058
LET'S SEE THE MONEY.

32:06.092 --> 32:07.793
Neal: SHERIFF!

32:07.826 --> 32:09.495
SHERIFF MORALES!

32:09.528 --> 32:11.797
I'M NEAL CAFFREY.
I'M THE ONE WITH THE BOUNTY.

32:11.830 --> 32:14.733
I'M THE GUY YOU'RE LOOKING FOR.

32:14.766 --> 32:16.969
I CAME TO THIS ISLAND
FOR SANCTUARY,

32:17.003 --> 32:19.505
AND THIS MAN SET ME UP.

32:29.815 --> 32:33.252
DOBBS HERE
LOADED ALL HIS MONEY --

32:33.285 --> 32:34.686
IT'S NOT TRUE.
LET HIM FINISH!

32:34.720 --> 32:36.588
HE LOADED HIS MONEY AND HIS
VALUABLES ONTO THE ESMERELDA

32:36.622 --> 32:38.124
AND WAS PLANNING TO RUN
WHILE EVERYONE WAS
STILL LOOKING FOR ME.

32:38.157 --> 32:40.526
YOU CAN'T POSSIBLY
BE BUYING THIS.

32:40.559 --> 32:42.794
HE'S BEING HUNTED
BY THE U.S. AUTHORITIES.

32:42.828 --> 32:44.096
WELL, THE BUREAU CHANGED
THEIR TARGET

32:44.130 --> 32:45.831
WHEN AGENT COLLINS DISCOVERED
WHO DOBBS REALLY IS.

32:45.864 --> 32:46.832
WHO'S THAT?

32:46.865 --> 32:48.100
ROBERT MACLEISH,

32:48.134 --> 32:51.703
NUMBER FOUR ON THE FBI's
"MOST WANTED" LIST.

32:51.737 --> 32:52.804
THAT'S A LIE.

32:52.838 --> 32:53.872
AND NOW THEY'RE AFTER
BOTH OF US.

32:53.905 --> 32:55.607
GET HIM OUT OF HERE.

32:55.641 --> 32:57.276
AGENT COLLINS IS AT THE COMPOUND
RIGHT NOW.

32:57.309 --> 32:58.777
SEE FOR YOURSELVES.
GET ME OUT OF HERE.
WE HAVE A DEAL.

32:58.810 --> 32:59.878
Collins:
NO SUDDEN MOVES!

32:59.911 --> 33:01.447
EVERYONE STAY CALM.

33:01.480 --> 33:02.781
LET'S GO, GUYS.

33:02.814 --> 33:03.949
CAFFREY.
[ GUN COCKS ]

33:03.982 --> 33:06.318
IT'S OVER.

33:12.658 --> 33:15.727
YOU GOT ME.

33:18.097 --> 33:20.699
MOVE IT, CAFFREY.

33:24.103 --> 33:26.438
EVERYONE HAS THEIR PRICE.

33:30.042 --> 33:32.411
I HOPE YOU GET EVERYTHING
YOU DESERVE.

33:32.444 --> 33:34.546
I'LL THINK OF YOU
WITH EVERY DOLLAR I SPEND.

33:34.580 --> 33:35.647
LET'S GO.

33:35.681 --> 33:38.150
WE HAVE A PLANE TO CATCH.

33:38.184 --> 33:41.453
[ VEHICLE DOOR CLOSES ]

33:47.193 --> 33:50.262
[ VEHICLE DOOR CLOSES,
ENGINE TURNS OVER ]

33:58.970 --> 34:01.373
[ RADIO CHATTER ]

34:02.574 --> 34:05.411
THERE'S MACLEISH.
THE PLAN WORKED.

34:05.444 --> 34:08.947
HE THINKS COLLINS
IS AFTER HIM, TOO.

34:08.980 --> 34:11.183
IT'S JUST NOT HIS DAY.

34:11.217 --> 34:12.618
WELL, HE'S HAD MORE GOOD ONES
THAN HE DESERVES.

34:14.453 --> 34:15.587
LAST CHANCE.

34:15.621 --> 34:18.790
YOU CAN GRAB A FREE FLIGHT BACK
TO NEW YORK.

34:18.824 --> 34:20.526
NO, THANKS.

34:20.559 --> 34:22.594
THE WORLD BECKONS.

34:22.628 --> 34:24.096
ANY PARTICULAR PART?

34:24.130 --> 34:28.300
SERIOUSLY?
JUST DON'T EXPECT A POSTCARD.

34:34.673 --> 34:37.876
MAKE SURE THE FEDS KEEP THE
BARGAIN THEY STRUCK WITH NEAL.

34:37.909 --> 34:39.878
HE TRUSTS YOU.

34:39.911 --> 34:41.880
I WILL.

34:41.913 --> 34:43.782
I KNOW.

34:51.022 --> 34:52.424
[ ENGINE SHUTS OFF ]

34:54.926 --> 34:57.463
Collins:
LOOK AT THIS, NEAL.

34:57.496 --> 34:58.897
AGENT BURKE'S BEEN WORRIED
ABOUT YOU.

34:58.930 --> 34:59.998
TRAVELED ALL THE WAY HERE

35:00.031 --> 35:01.099
AND ALMOST DIDN'T GET
TO SAY GOOD-BYE.

35:01.133 --> 35:04.002
GOOD TO SEE YOU AGAIN,
PETER.
YOU TOO.

35:04.035 --> 35:06.672
CONGRATULATIONS.
YOU CAUGHT HIM.

35:06.705 --> 35:08.640
PLAN ON TAKING HIM BACK
ON MY CHARTER?

35:08.674 --> 35:10.676
[ SCOFFS ]
YOU'RE NOT GONNA STOP ME.

35:10.709 --> 35:11.743
NO?

35:11.777 --> 35:13.645
YOU SHOULD KNOW WHO ELSE
IS ON THAT PLANE.

35:13.679 --> 35:15.481
WHAT ARE YOU TRYING
TO PULL, BURKE?

35:15.514 --> 35:18.150
NOTHING.
HENRY DOBBS IS ON THAT PLANE.

35:18.184 --> 35:20.085
HAD A FEELING
HE'D BE NEEDING A FLIGHT.

35:20.118 --> 35:21.287
I DON'T GIVE A DAMN
ABOUT DOBBS.

35:21.320 --> 35:22.521
OH, I THINK YOU DO,

35:22.554 --> 35:24.156
BECAUSE "DOBBS"
IS AN ALIAS.

35:24.190 --> 35:25.757
YOU PROBABLY KNOW HIM
BY HIS REAL NAME --

35:25.791 --> 35:26.925
ROB MACLEISH.

35:26.958 --> 35:29.628
DOBBS IS ROBERT MACLEISH?

35:29.661 --> 35:30.929
THE ONE AND ONLY.

35:30.962 --> 35:33.265
YOU PLAY THIS RIGHT,

35:33.299 --> 35:35.601
AND YOU'VE LANDED
THE BIGGEST SCORE OF YOUR LIFE.

35:35.634 --> 35:38.604
ROBERT MACLEISH IS ON
THIS PLANE, RIGHT NOW?

35:38.637 --> 35:40.272
YEP.

35:40.306 --> 35:42.274
JUSTICE DEPARTMENT
HAS BEEN FULLY BRIEFED.

35:42.308 --> 35:44.109
THERE WILL BE CAMERAS
AND REPORTERS

35:44.142 --> 35:46.278
WHEN WE LAND
ON THE CANARY ISLANDS,

35:46.312 --> 35:48.847
WHICH, FUNNY ENOUGH,
DOES HAVE EXTRADITION.

35:48.880 --> 35:52.518
NOW, YOU CAN SAY THAT YOU HAD
NOTHING TO DO WITH HIS CAPTURE.

35:52.551 --> 35:54.620
WHY GIVE NEAL
ALL THE CREDIT

35:54.653 --> 35:56.988
WHEN WE'VE GONE THROUGH
ALL THIS WORK TO INCLUDE YOU?

35:57.022 --> 35:58.457
Neal:
SEE THE PART WHERE YOU, UH,

35:58.490 --> 36:00.326
SECRETLY RECRUITED ME
TO HELP YOU TAKE DOWN MACLEISH?

36:00.359 --> 36:02.794
THAT'S GOOD THINKING.

36:02.828 --> 36:04.230
YOU SET ME UP.

36:04.263 --> 36:05.531
FOR THE WIN.

36:05.564 --> 36:07.566
AND WHAT DO YOU
GET OUT OF THIS, CAFFREY?

36:09.100 --> 36:10.702
MY OLD DESK BACK.

36:10.736 --> 36:12.538
[ CHUCKLES ]

36:12.571 --> 36:14.340
Collins: WELL, MY JOB
WAS TO BRING YOU BACK.

36:14.373 --> 36:15.907
WHAT HAPPENS TO YOU
ONCE YOU'RE IN THE SYSTEM,

36:15.941 --> 36:17.142
THAT'S UP TO THE BUREAU.

36:17.175 --> 36:18.977
DON'T TRY IT, DOBBS.

36:19.010 --> 36:21.313
[ GUN COCKS ]
BACK AWAY FROM THE DOOR,
MACLEISH.

36:21.347 --> 36:23.415
NO MORE RUNNING.

36:23.449 --> 36:25.351
I'M HAULING YOUR ASS BACK
TO NEW YORK.

36:28.053 --> 36:29.921
[ JET ENGINE WHIRRING ]

36:29.955 --> 36:32.358
YOU HEAR THAT?

36:32.391 --> 36:35.227
WE'RE GOING HOME.

36:37.863 --> 36:39.265
WE'RE GOING HOME.

36:53.211 --> 36:54.680
Neal: SHOULD BE OFF THE CANE
IN A WEEK.

36:54.713 --> 36:55.614
YOU THINK SO?

36:55.647 --> 36:56.682
MAYBE.
YEAH.

36:56.715 --> 36:57.549
Jones: CAFFREY.

36:59.885 --> 37:01.353
WELCOME BACK.

37:01.387 --> 37:02.754
THANK YOU, JONES.

37:02.788 --> 37:05.857
THANK YOU BOTH
FOR BRINGING ME BACK.

37:05.891 --> 37:07.259
YOU KNOW, I ALWAYS THOUGHT
I'D BE THE ONE

37:07.293 --> 37:08.260
TO SHOOT YOU IN THE LEG.

37:08.294 --> 37:10.429
[ CHUCKLES SARCASTICALLY ]

37:10.462 --> 37:13.299
WELL, THERE'S
ALWAYS NEXT TIME.

37:13.332 --> 37:15.301
WELL, I HOPE
YOU GET A "NEXT TIME."

37:15.334 --> 37:17.068
WHAT HE DID,
HE DID FOR PETER.

37:17.102 --> 37:18.870
YEAH.

37:18.904 --> 37:20.706
I GET THAT.

37:20.739 --> 37:23.141
LOOKS LIKE YOU GOT
SOMETHING SPECIAL.

37:23.174 --> 37:25.577
ASIDE FROM THE BEARD.

37:27.946 --> 37:29.381
HUH.

37:29.415 --> 37:31.450
A LETTER OF APPRECIATION.

37:31.483 --> 37:33.919
I'LL HAVE TO GET IT FRAMED.

37:33.952 --> 37:35.153
HE'S MAD
BECAUSE I DENIED HIM

37:35.186 --> 37:36.555
THE REWARD MONEY
FOR MACLEISH.

37:36.588 --> 37:38.557
OH.

37:38.590 --> 37:39.958
A MEDAL WOULD HAVE BEEN NICE.
THAT'S ALL I'M SAYING.

37:39.991 --> 37:42.794
WELL, YOU KNOW,
SPEAKING OF MEDAL, JONES --

37:42.828 --> 37:45.130
YEAH, CAFFREY.

37:45.163 --> 37:46.998
YOUGET A MEDAL.

37:47.032 --> 37:48.099
[ DRAWER OPENS ]

37:48.133 --> 37:50.602
[ JONES CLEARS THROAT ]

37:50.636 --> 37:54.973
AND THE AWARD FOR THE BEST
FOREIGN CAPTURE GOES TO...

37:55.006 --> 37:56.742
NEAL CAFFREY.

37:56.775 --> 37:57.576
[ CHUCKLES ]

37:57.609 --> 37:59.611
MAY I?
YEAH, OF COURSE.

38:01.480 --> 38:02.914
[ ANKLET BEEPS ]

38:02.948 --> 38:05.183
COMFORTABLE?

38:05.216 --> 38:07.586
YEAH.
FEELS LIKE HOME.

38:07.619 --> 38:08.987
GOOD.

38:18.964 --> 38:21.767
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

38:21.800 --> 38:24.102
ELLEN.

38:24.135 --> 38:25.103
OH, DON'T GET UP.

38:25.136 --> 38:27.172
I'M FINE.
IT'S JUST ANNOYING.

38:27.205 --> 38:28.306
[ CHUCKLES ]

38:28.340 --> 38:29.475
OH, IT'S SO GOOD
TO SEE YOU, NEAL.

38:29.508 --> 38:32.344
YOU TOO.
OH...

38:32.378 --> 38:35.781
SO, I MADE THE RIGHT DECISION
TRUSTING PETER.

38:35.814 --> 38:37.315
YOU'VE ALWAYS HAD
A PRETTY GOOD INSTINCT.

38:37.349 --> 38:39.385
YOU TOO.

38:39.418 --> 38:41.219
JUNE SAID SHE NEVER
EVEN CONSIDERED

38:41.252 --> 38:43.121
RENTING OUT YOUR ROOM
AFTER YOU LEFT.

38:43.154 --> 38:44.956
WELL, SHE IS
ONE OF THE MANY REASONS

38:44.990 --> 38:47.693
THAT I'M GLAD TO BE BACK.

38:47.726 --> 38:51.029
WANT TO SIT DOWN?
CAN I GET YOU SOMETHING?

38:51.062 --> 38:54.966
THE MARSHALS ARE SHIPPING ME OFF
IN A FEW WEEKS.

38:55.000 --> 38:56.568
WHERE?

38:56.602 --> 38:59.871
NOWHERE CLOSE, I'M AFRAID.

38:59.905 --> 39:03.341
THERE'S BEEN
TOO MUCH EXPOSURE HERE.

39:05.176 --> 39:07.513
A FEW WEEKS, HUH?

39:08.580 --> 39:11.817
BOTH OF US GET
ANOTHER NEW START.

39:11.850 --> 39:12.851
YEAH.

39:15.053 --> 39:18.089
I WAS REALLY HOPING
WE'D HAVE MORE TIME TOGETHER.

39:18.123 --> 39:20.392
ME TOO.

39:22.528 --> 39:24.830
EVEN THOUGH I HAVEN'T SEEN YOU
IN A FEW YEARS,

39:24.863 --> 39:27.332
YOU ARE THE CLOSEST THING
THAT I HAVE TO FAMILY.

39:27.365 --> 39:28.900
OH, THAT'S NOT TRUE.

39:28.934 --> 39:30.368
YOU KNOW WHAT I MEAN.

39:30.402 --> 39:33.104
THEY DON'T KNOW
ABOUT OUR HISTORY.

39:33.138 --> 39:35.373
THEY DON'T KNOW
ABOUT MY DAD.

39:35.407 --> 39:37.409
THEY DON'T NEED TO.

39:37.443 --> 39:39.678
BUTDO.

39:39.711 --> 39:42.047
THAT WAS
A LONG TIME AGO, NEAL.

39:42.080 --> 39:45.451
THERE IS NO REASON
TO GO DREDGING IT UP AGAIN.

39:45.484 --> 39:48.119
EVERYTHING I GREW UP
BELIEVING WAS WRONG.

39:48.153 --> 39:50.789
EVERYTHING.

39:50.822 --> 39:53.391
AND I RAN BEFORE I GOT TO HEAR
THE FULL STORY.

39:53.425 --> 39:55.527
I'M NOT RUNNING ANYMORE.

39:55.561 --> 39:57.295
I WANT TO KNOW WHO HE WAS.

39:57.328 --> 39:59.865
BEFORE I LEAVE --

39:59.898 --> 40:02.133
I PROMISE.

40:02.167 --> 40:04.102
YOU PROMISE?

40:04.135 --> 40:06.572
I PROMISE.

40:06.605 --> 40:10.375
BUT TONIGHT,
TELL ME ABOUT THE ISLAND.

40:10.408 --> 40:12.644
WAS THERE A GIRL?

40:12.678 --> 40:16.915
YEAH, HER, UH --
HER NAME WAS MAYA.

40:22.454 --> 40:24.590
YOU SPOKE WITH CAFFREY
ON THE PHONE.

40:24.623 --> 40:27.092
YOU HAD A MAP WITH HIS LOCATION
CIRCLED ON IT.

40:27.125 --> 40:29.761
THE BOARD WANTS TO KNOW
HOW THAT CAME TO PASS.

40:29.795 --> 40:31.797
REESE,
I DIDN'T AID OR ABET.

40:31.830 --> 40:33.732
I DIDN'T KNOW WHERE HE WAS,

40:33.765 --> 40:36.468
SO I MADE THE PHONE CALL
TO TRACK HIM.

40:36.502 --> 40:38.570
KRAMER HAD IT OUT
FOR CAFFREY,

40:38.604 --> 40:41.773
AND THEN YOU, AFTER YOU
HELPED HIM RETURN THE RAPHAEL.

40:41.807 --> 40:43.241
I KNOW.

40:43.274 --> 40:44.342
CAFFREY'S CASE HAS RISEN

40:44.375 --> 40:46.912
TO THE LEVEL OF DEPUTY DIRECTOR
AND INSPECTOR GENERAL,

40:46.945 --> 40:49.481
AND A LOT OF YOUR WORK IS BEING
PUT UNDER THE MICROSCOPE.

40:49.515 --> 40:52.618
YOU WERE EXPRESSLY ORDERED
OFF NEAL'S CASE.

40:52.651 --> 40:54.185
YOU BROKE THE RULES.

40:54.219 --> 40:55.654
I UNDERSTAND.

40:55.687 --> 40:57.623
AND AS FAR
AS D.C. IS CONCERNED,

40:57.656 --> 41:00.458
IT WAS COLLINS WHO HELPED
CAFFREY BRING HOME MACLEISH,

41:00.492 --> 41:03.161
NOT YOU.

41:07.733 --> 41:09.535
NOW THAT NEAL IS BACK,

41:09.568 --> 41:11.269
I WILL MAKE SURE
THAT BOTH OF US

41:11.302 --> 41:12.871
STAY ON THE STRAIGHT
AND NARROW.

41:12.904 --> 41:16.875
AFRAID WE'RE PAST THAT,
PETER.

41:21.312 --> 41:23.782
Neal: SO THEN MAYA TELLS DOBBS
EXACTLY WHERE WE WERE.

41:23.815 --> 41:25.450
REALLY?
YEAH. SHE WAS IN ON IT.

41:25.483 --> 41:26.952
IT WAS ALL PART
OF THE PLAN.

41:26.985 --> 41:28.186
AHH. WOW.

41:28.219 --> 41:30.355
EVERYTHING ALL RIGHT?

41:30.388 --> 41:33.992
NO.
I'VE BEEN REASSIGNED.

41:34.025 --> 41:36.494
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

41:36.528 --> 41:41.700
IT MEANS I'M NO LONGER
WORKING WHITE COLLAR.
